<i># Ah #</i>

40:01.132 --> 40:04.499
<i># Ah, ahh, ah #</i>

40:04.568 --> 40:07.731
<i># Ah, ahh, ah #</i>

40:07.805 --> 40:11.138
<i># Ah, ahh, ah #</i>

40:11.208 --> 40:14.541
<i># Ah, ahh, ah #</i>

40:14.612 --> 40:16.746
<i># Ahh, ah #</i>

40:21.452 --> 40:25.889
<i># I look at the cross #</i>

40:28.793 --> 40:32.661
<i># Then I look away... #</i>

40:43.841 --> 40:44.941
Sydney.

40:44.942 --> 40:47.442
Don't.

40:48.112 --> 40:50.612
There's nothing you can say.

40:59.824 --> 41:00.890
Sloane is dead.

41:00.891 --> 41:03.758
We can now locate The Passenger
without his interference.

41:03.828 --> 41:05.161
Not quite.

41:05.162 --> 41:09.121
The code key you retrieved
from the CIA is unusable.

41:09.200 --> 41:12.033
I can only assume that was
deliberate on their part.

41:12.102 --> 41:14.170
Vaughn played you.

41:14.171 --> 41:16.439
He's likely to try again.

41:16.440 --> 41:19.238
But that will be
his last mistake.

41:53.077 --> 41:55.411
I'm surprised you didn't get
the reference.

41:55.412 --> 41:58.575
Modified Kayexalate cocktail
washed with tetrodotoxin

41:58.649 --> 42:03.086
presented in a bottle
of Chambertin-Clos de Bèze.

42:03.687 --> 42:06.187
Just like we used in Saigon.

42:10.261 --> 42:11.861
But understand,

42:11.862 --> 42:14.695
this was not done
out of compassion.

42:14.765 --> 42:20.362
I orchestrated this because,
and only because,

42:20.437 --> 42:22.937
I need you.

